cess_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aOriginating from papers presented at an international colloquium, the 18 articles in this volume reflect the different aspects of modality: general, lexical, temporal and modal. There is no one single definition or methodological approach to the study of modality. This is borne out by the range of these articles, with perspectives extending from different manifestation forms of modality to its different implications or values (alethic, deontic, epistemic, radical, etc.) and from modality in specific genres to contrastive and historical perspectives on the phenomenon.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aModality (Linguistics)vCongresses. 4aFranzösisch. 4aKongress. 4aModalität ‹Linguistik›. 4aOdense ‹2000›. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBirkelund, Merete, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirkelund, Merete, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlanche-Benveniste, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumenthal, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoysen, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoysen, Gerhard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDesclés, Jean-Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerslund, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKampers-Manhe, Brigitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKjærsgaard, Poul Søren, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKjœrsgaard, Poul Søren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorzen, Han